It looks like this board is really junk. I've already ordered a larger one, hoping it can solve the problem.
Take a look at what I found in the workshop.
This is a 24-volt solar panel. Unfortunately, the sun is too low (and there's also a tree blocking it), so as soon as I connected a load, the voltage dropped almost to zero.
It looks like I'll have to wait until tomorrow to find out if this solar panel is sufficient, or if I need that higher-performance solar panel I ordered.
The information on Amazon shows that this solar panel was bought in 2021, with a maximum output of 12 volts at 1.2 amps.
So, either this solar panel is faulty, or my multimeter is faulty, or they changed the product page.
Hello everyone, there's some good news!
